{{Infobox person | name = '''Baba Buddha ji''' | image = File:Guru Arjun Dev being pronounced fifth guru.jpg | alt = | caption = Baba Buddha coronating the fifth guru | birth_name = | birth_date = 6 October 1506 | birth_place = Amritsar, India | death_date = {{Death date and age|1631|09|08|1506|10|06|df=yes}} | death_place = Ramdas Village | years_active = 1506-1631 | known_for = Early figure of [[Sikhism]] | successor = | parents = Bhai Sukha Randhava, Mai Gauran | spouse = }} {{Sikhism sidebar}}
'''Baba Buddha ji''' (6 October 1506 – 8 September 1631) was a prime figure in early [[Sikhism]]. He was one of the earliest disciples of [[Guru Nanak]]. He performed the formal coronation ceremonies of 5 Sikh gurus, till [[Guru Hargobind]]. It is said that in his childhood, he was blessed with a long life by Guru Nanak, who named him as Buddha (meaning - Old/Aged Man) after he was amused by his mature queries related to spirituality at such at young age.{{citation needed|date=December 2016}} While the English spelling is same, the word Buddha here is different than [[Gautam Buddha]] of [[Buddhism]]. With Baba Buddha Ji, "d" in the word Buddha is pronounced as it is, while with Gautam Buddha, "d" is pronounced with tongue touching the teeth (pronounced like "the").
