{{More citations needed|date=July 2010}} '''Hazer Tarkhan''' was a general ([[tarkhan]] is both a military rank and, in some cases, a personal name) who led a [[Khazar]] army of 40,000 men in the failed defense of [[Atil]] in 737 CE. He was ambushed and killed by Kawthar, the lieutenant of Marwan ibn Muhammad (later [[Caliph]] [[Marwan II]]). Following his death the Khazars sued for peace.
