'''Omberto Aldobrandeschi''' (? - 1259), as a member of the [[Aldobrandeschi family]], is a Count of Santafiore in the Maremma of Siena.<ref>{{cite book | year=2010 | page= 660 | title=Dante Encyclopedia |publisher=Routledge}}</ref> Counts of Santafiore are usually in wars against the city of Siena. In 1259, Omberto was killed in one of these battles, at the village of Campagnatico. Omberto is mentioned in Canto XI of Purgatorio of [[Divine Comedy]] by Dante, as an example of a sinner of pride.<ref>{{cite book | title=Divine Comedy |first=Dante | last= Alighieri |at=Canto XI of Purgatory}}</ref>
