{{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}}
'''Peter of Bourbon-La Marche''' (1342&ndash;1362, [[Lyon]]) was the eldest son of [[James I, Count of La Marche]] and Jeanne of Châtillon.

He was knighted by his father shortly before the [[Battle of Brignais]], in which both father and son fought. Both were severely wounded during the battle, but were carried away by their soldiers to Lyon. He survived his father only a short while, and was succeeded by his brother [[John I, Count of La Marche|John]].

